GSD.description: Spoofer 1.4.6 suffers from unquoted service paths vulnerability. An attacker as a low privileged local user can hijack the execution flow of the application to escalate privileges by inserting a malicious executable in a higher level directory with the vulnerable path.

Spoofer 1.4.6 suffers from unquoted service paths vulnerability. An attacker as a low privileged local user can hijack the execution flow of the application to escalate privileges by inserting a malicious executable in a higher level directory with the vulnerable path.
